about:
Play the best chat games for Discord: Uno, Hangman, Pets and more! Works in a server with friends or in direct messages with the bot.
The objective is to bring the most entertainment to you and your group, with the least amount of hassle and spam possible.

<:gamecube:761373355742986290> Use the command **{prefix}help** for a list of commands and games.
<:staff:412019879772815361> You can contact the developer [here](https://discord.gg/hGHnfda) or by using **{prefix}feedback [message]**
<:github:409803419717599234> Take a look at the [GitHub repository](https://github.com/Samrux/Pac-Man-Bot)
welcome:
Thanks for inviting Pac-Man Bot!
Enjoy some of the best chat games for Discord: Uno, Hangman, Pets and more! 

The default prefix is **{prefix}**
Send **{prefix}help** to see a list of commands you can use. Send **{prefix}help [command]** to see detailed help about a specific command.
gameHelp:
```css
#Controls:
This game is played in turns by adding or removing a reaction. The arrow emotes will move Pac-Man, and the skip emote will toggle fast-forward mode. In fast-forward mode, the arrows move Pac-Man until you reach an intersection or hit something.
To win, you must collect all the pellets, while avoiding the ghosts. Try to get a high score!

#Commands: @
"{prefix}display" - Switch between normal and slim mode
"{prefix}bump" - Move game message to the bottom of the chat
"{prefix}cancel" - End the game unless someone is playing;

#Tips:
• Each eaten ghost during the same power mode yields twice as many points as the last!
• Eat the fruit that spawns after eating a large amount of pellets for extra points!
• Blinky chases you, Pinky tries to ambush you, Inky will follow Blinky's lead, and Clyde is kind of shy. 4 times during the game they will scatter and stop chasing you.
• The ghosts can't turn 180º unless they're Eatable or switching modes

@ 'Add any reaction to return to the game'
```
customHelp:
You can play Pac-Man using your own custom maps!
Send **{prefix}custompacman [map]** to start a custom game (where "[map]" is your custom map)
If you want, you can put your map between triple backticks (\`\`\`) to keep it organized in a code block.

**__Creating a map__**
Anything but a space or a special character will become a solid wall. Maps must contain *some* space to move through, and can't be longer than 1500 characters.
List of special characters:
 `O`: Pac-Man
 `G`: Ghosts, up to 4
 `-`: Ghost box door
 `•` and `o`: Pellet and Super Pellet
 `$`: Fruit (left tile)
 `~`: A pellet, but ghosts can't move here from below
 `_`: Empty, but ghosts can't move here from below
